<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>⚔️ Session Fixation Application ⚔️</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>

    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-EVSTQN3/azprG1Anm3QDgpJLIm9Nao0Yz1ztcQTwFspd3yD65VohhpuuCOmLASjC" crossorigin="anonymous">

    <%= javascript_importmap_tags %>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-MrcW6ZMFYlzcLA8Nl+NtUVF0sA7MsXsP1UyJoMp4YLEuNSfAP+JcXn/tWtIaxVXM" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script>
      document.addEventListener("turbo:load", function() {
        const alert = document.getElementById('flash-alert');
        if (alert) {
          setTimeout(() => {
            alert.classList.remove('show');
            alert.classList.add('fade');
            setTimeout(() => alert.remove(), 150); 
          }, 5000);
        }
      });
    </script>
    <style>
      .alert-custom {
        max-height: 0; 
        opacity: 0; 
        transition: max-height 0.5s ease, opacity 0.5s ease;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .alert.show {
        max-height: 100px;
        opacity: 1; 
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body class="bg-dark text-light">
  <% if @search_val %>
    <%== @search_val %></center>
  <% end %>

    <div class="container">
      <br>
      <center><h1 class="mb-4" style="color: #AA336A">⚔️ RoR Session Fixation Application ⚔️</h1></center>
      <div class="table-responsive">
        <table class="table table-sm table-striped table-hover table-bordered mx-auto" style="max-width: 100%; height: 290px;">
          <thead class="table-info">
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Your Anonymous Session ID</th>
              <th scope="col">Your Signed and Encrypted Session Cookie</th>
              <th scope="col">Your session object ID</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="text-light">
              <td style="word-wrap: break-word; max-width: 150px;"><%= session.id %></td>
              <td style="word-wrap: break-word; max-width: 300px;"><%= cookies[:_session_fixation_application_session] %></td>
              <td style="word-wrap: break-word; max-width: 150px;"><%= session.object_id %></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-warning" style="max-width: 100%; margin: auto;">
        <p>
          <strong>Session Object ID:</strong> This ID changes with each page refresh because it represents the current state of the session data, which may be modified during interactions. Each request can create a new instance of the session object as data is updated or processed. The cookie changes in each request as Rails 7 uses a rotating cookie jar with a new encryption initialization vector for request each and sets the new cookie. The session ID however does not change between requests.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Session ID:</strong> In contrast, the session ID is a stable identifier stored in a cookie that remains consistent throughout your session. It allows the server to track your interactions and retrieve the appropriate session data across multiple requests.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <%= yield %>
    <br>
  </body>
</html>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('turbo:load', function() {
    // Check if the session ID is nil
    const sessionId = "<%= session.id %>";
    const search_param = "<%= params[:search] %>";

    if (!sessionId) { // Refresh only if session.id is nil
      location.reload();
    }
    if (search_param) { // Refresh only if session.id is nil
      window.location.href = window.location.href.split('?')[0];
    }
  });
</script>


